<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-07"><hi rend="italic">September 7,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1145.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your cable dispatch of the 6th instant has
                            been received, as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Aguirre just released and Sanguily’s case will be tried soon.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Mr. Aguirre’s friends have been informed of his release. Your report of
                            the circumstances of his enlargement are awaited before commenting on
                            this tardy relief of a citizen of the United States confined under
                            conditions which have enlisted the lively sympathy and earnest efforts
                            of this Government in his behalf.</p>
                        <p>You will continue to press for speedy and equitable treatment of
                            Sanguily’s case.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>